<p>A post shared by  Gabrielle Union-Wade (<?php echo e('@'); ?>gabunion) on Sep 20, 2020 at 6:17pm PDT</p>

<p>The no-audience event was hosted by Jimmy Kimmel at LA's Staples Center, while winners accepted their awards from their homes for the first time to adhere to California's social distancing rules amid the pandemic. </p>

<p>While standing in front of a mirror and applying makeup, Gabrielle broke out in verses in honor of the popular HBO program created by Issa Rae.</p>

<p>Bouncy curls framed her flawless face and she wore a white shower cap with black polka dots holding back her hair. </p>

<p>Toward the end of her freestyle, Dwyane stumbles upon his wife as she praises the program because 'they show the boys booties,' referring to the male nudity on Insecure. </p>

<p>Star power: The 47-year-old actress looked fresh-faced while she joked about launching her rap career as she sang a few lines for the virtual show</p>

<p>Fan: While standing in front of a mirror and applying makeup, Gabrielle broke out in verses in honor of the popular HBO program created by Issa Rae</p>

<p>'Rap career launched. Your welcome,' she captioned the video on Instagram. 'Its no secret we are huge Insecure fans so this was hella fun to do. Always winners in our house and in our hearts. Here's our bit in full. Love yall.'</p>

<p>The show was nominated for Outstanding Comedy Series, Lead Actress - Comedy Series, and Supporting Actress - Comedy Series, but ultimately lost out to the cast of Schitt's Creek.</p>

<p>Gabrielle covered a range of topics on Naomi Campbell's latest web series, No Filter, including Union's exit from America's Got Talent earlier this year and the ensuing investigation surrounding her departure. </p>

<p>'When you walk in to a space and you recognize that change needs to happen sooner than later, [it's important] to speak up,' Gabrielle stated. </p>

